commit.message: Prepare v2.2.0 release
Merge branch 'fix-typing'

Refrain from adding Details to backoff namespace

If needed, I want to make sure we put this in the right place. There
may ultimately be some other types which it would be helpful to expose
as well, and in that case I think it might be better to have a typing
submodule where only these types are exposed.
Merge branch 'add-exception-to-details'

Improve type hints for runtime, constant wait gens

This generators will work fine with floats for arguments. In the type
hinting world, float can be used to mean int or float.
Make flake8 happy with line lengths

commit.message:
Improve type annotation for backoff.expo

`backoff.expo` accepts floats. Most usage in our codebase has a floating point `factor`. If we want to preserve exact inference in cases where the return type is `Generator[int, Any, None` we could use an overload (TypeVar could work, but would be a little worse for cases involving defaults).

Improve type annotation for backoff.expo

`backoff.expo` accepts floats. Most usage in our codebase has a floating point `factor`. If we want to preserve exact inference in cases where the return type is `Generator[int, Any, None` we could use an overload (TypeVar could work, but would be a little worse for cases involving defaults).

commit.message: Prepare 2.1.2 release

Don't use importlib.metadata for __version__

Fixes https://github.com/litl/backoff/issues/166
Prepare 2.1.1 release

Use importlib.metadata to set __version__

This way we don't have to remember to update the version in two places
every release.  The version will only need to be set in pyproject.toml

Use maybe-called keyword values everywhere

We were still passing in the maybe callable original arg rather than
using the looked-up value in a couple places.

Improve callable kwarg tests

This would have caught a bug where we were passing the original
non-called kwarg to _next_wait.
Update async to lookup callabale kwargs every time
Fix async test
